MACINTOSH IIci

•	What year was it made? --- 1991
•	What operating system does it run? --- System 6.0.4-7.6.1
•	How much did it cost (then and now, adjusted for inflation)? How hard is it to find one on the secondhand market (check eBay and Craig’s List). --- It originally cost $5369 ($9896.39 inflation adjusted). On eBay, it costs $39.99-$549. On craigslist, there is one Macintosh IIci listed for $150. 
•	In brief (a short paragraph), what were its historical strengths and weaknesses as a platform? What was it best known for? --- Regardless of the price, it keeps the record of robust four years before the invention of new model. It is known for exapandability, as its card slots that would be connected to ethernet, audio, video.  

Turn it on (you must figure out how). Open WordPerfect. Open MS Word. Try typing a simple document in each. Which do you like better, and why? Open MacPaint. Try drawing something. (You don’t need to save any of your work from these applications.) What else is on this Mac? What can you learn about its past user(s)? --- The switch is on the keyboard. WordPerfect has its navigation icons on the left side and MS Word on its top. WordPerfect's navigation is iconographic compared to that of descriptive navigation of MS Word. McPaint allows a composition of shapes and fonts with various patterns, shades, sides. There is even an option to set the color of patters (either RGB ir YCM) but that cannot be displayed given the monitor does not accomodate color display. Gird and ruler system reminds me of an elementary photoshop software. 

